    Featured Projects:

    Digital

    Murakami.Flowers System

    In my Communication Design class, I developed a visual communication design system for Murakami.Flowers, an NFT collection using Takashi Murakami's iconic flower motif.  The end result was a design system, magazine spread, and Instagram ad. 

    View More

    UI/UX

    Pet Simulator - Hack112 Hackathon Winning Project

    My team created a cute pet-simulator game, incorporating sentiment analysis and web-scraping. I designed and illustrated all the visual elements of the project. This project won 1st place among 18 teams, and over 100 people.

    View More

    Product

    Promotional Robot

    I made this as a way to store stickers and business cards for my robotics team. It held business cards in its hands, and a roll of stickers was stored inside the body that came out of the mouth like a tape dispenser. Made via CAD and 3D Printing.
